<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Safe Preview</title>
  <style>
    body { font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background:#f8fafc; color:#0f172a; margin:0; }
    .wrap { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 32px 20px; }
    .panel, .preview-card { background:#fff; border:1px solid #cbd5e1; border-radius:16px; padding:24px; }
    .preview-card { margin-top:20px; }
    .classic { border-top:8px solid #0f766e; }
    .modern { border-top:8px solid #2563eb; }
    .festival { border-top:8px solid #ea580c; }
    .badge { display:inline-block; background:#e2e8f0; padding:6px 10px; border-radius:999px; font-size:12px; font-weight:700; margin-bottom:14px; }
    a { color:#0f766e; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="panel">
      <h1>Safe Preview</h1>
      <p>This route renders variables through a normal EJS view instead of evaluating attacker-controlled template syntax inside a newly created template string.</p>
      <p><a href="/">Back to home</a></p>
    </div>

    <div class="preview-card <%= style %>">
      <div class="badge">Safe Mode</div>
      <h2>Greeting for <%= name %></h2>
      <p><%= message %></p>
      <small>Generated safely by Greeting Studio</small>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>